Air France, BNP, Cybergun, Gifi, Sopra: French Equity Preview

-- B y   A n d r e w   R o b e r t s
-- 
2011-06-09T04:01:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-08/air-france-bnp-cybergun-gifi-sopra-french-equity-preview.html
The following is a list of companies
whose stocks may have unusual changes in Paris. Symbols are in
parentheses after company names and prices are from the last
close.  France’s CAC 40 Index fell 0.9 percent to 3,837.98. The
broader SBF 120 Index also declined 0.9 percent to 2,901.94.  Air France-KLM (AF)  Group: Europe’s biggest airline said
it had a 4.9 percent increase in May passenger traffic from a
year earlier and a 1.4 percent decline in cargo traffic. The
shares fell 2.4 percent to 10.80 euros.  BNP Paribas (BNP)  : Ageas (AGS BB) and BGL BNP Paribas
agreed to merge their jointly-owned Luxembourg life insurance
unit with Cardif Lux International, the Luxembourg life
insurance subsidiary of BNP Paribas Cardif. BNP Paribas declined
0.8 percent to 52.21 euros.  Cybergun SA (CYB FP): The maker of plastic guns said full
year net income rose to 4 million euros ($5.8 million) from 3
million euros a year earlier. The shares fell 0.3 percent to
14.01 euros.  Gifi (IGF)  : The discount chain maintained its full year
objectives after first-half net income declined to 23.8 million
euros from 27.9 million euros a year earlier. The shares were
unchanged at 82.29 euros.  Plastivaloire (PVL)  : The manufacturer of plastics for
cars and fittings for flat-screen TVs said first-half net income
rose to 42.7 million euros from 3.4 million euros a year
earlier. The shares declined 0.2 percent to 24.75 euros.  Sopra Group SA (SOP)  : The consulting and computer-
services company said shareholders approved the exceptional
distribution of share premiums and reserves in the form of 3.92
euros in cash and the project to spin off Axway. The shares
gained 0.3 percent to 84.60 euros.  To contact the reporter on this story:
